 } } \right| = 0$$<br><br>$$\Rightarrow$$ $$\alpha$$($$\beta$$ $$-$$ $$\gamma$$) $$-$$ $$\alpha$$(0 $$-$$ $$\gamma$$) + $$\gamma$$(0 $$-$$ $$\gamma$$) = 0<br><br>$$\Rightarrow$$ $$\alpha$$$$\beta$$ $$-$$ $$\alpha$$$$\gamma$$ + $$\alpha$$$$\gamma$$ $$-$$ $$\gamma$$<sup>2</sup> = 0<br><br>$$\Rightarrow$$ $$\gamma$$<sup>2</sup> = $$\alpha$$$$\beta$$<br><br>Hence, $$\gamma$$ is GM of $$\alpha$$ and $$\beta$$.

Given, $$F = 3\widehat i + 2\widehat j - 4\widehat k$$<br><br>$$\because$$ F is applied at the point (1, $$-$$1, 2), we have to find moment of the force about the point (2, $$-$$1, 3).<br><br>$$\therefore$$ Position vector,<br><br>$$r = (\widehat i - \widehat j + 2\widehat k) - (2\widehat i - \widehat j + 3\widehat k) =  - \widehat i - \widehat k$$<br><br>$$\therefore$$ Moment, $$M = r \times F = \left| {\matrix{
   {\widehat i} &amp; {\widehat j} &amp; {\widehat k}  \cr 
   { - 1} &amp; 0 &amp; { - 1}  \cr 
   3 &amp; 2 &amp; { - 4}  \cr 

 } } \right|$$<br><br>$$ = \widehat i(0 + 2) - \widehat j(4 + 3) + \widehat k( - 2 - 0)$$<br><br>$$ = 2\widehat i - 7\widehat j - 2\widehat k$$

Let $$a = \widehat i + \widehat j + \widehat k$$ and $$b = 2\widehat i + 3\widehat j - \widehat k$$<br><br>Clearly, the vector which is orthogonal to both the vectors, is <br><br>$$a \times b = \left| {\matrix{
   {\widehat i} &amp; {\widehat j} &amp; {\widehat k}  \cr 
   1 &amp; 1 &amp; 1  \cr 
   2 &amp; 3 &amp; { - 1}  \cr 

 } } \right|$$<br><br>$$ = \widehat i( - 1 - 3) - \widehat j( - 1 - 2) + \widehat k(3 - 2)$$<br><br>$$ =  - 4\widehat i + 3\widehat j + \widehat k$$<br><br>Now, required vector = Unit vector along a $$\times$$ b<br><br>$$ = {{ - 4\widehat i + 3\widehat j + \widehat k} \over {\sqrt {{{( - 4)}^2} + {{(3)}^2} + {1^2}} }} = {{ - 4\widehat i + 3\widehat j + \widehat k} \over {\sqrt {26} }}$$

Let diagonals of a parallelogram are $${d_1} = 3\widehat i + \widehat j - 2\widehat k$$ and $${d_2} = \widehat i - 3\widehat j + 4\widehat k$$<br><br>Area of parallelogram $$ = {1 \over 2}\left| {{d_1} \times {d_2}} \right|$$<br><br>Then, $${d_1} \times {d_2} = \left| {\matrix{
   {\widehat i} &amp; {\widehat j} &amp; {\widehat k}  \cr 
   3 &amp; 1 &amp; { - 2}  \cr 
   1 &amp; { - 3} &amp; 4  \cr 

 } } \right|$$<br><br>$$ = \widehat i(4 - 6) - \widehat j(12 + 2) + \widehat k( - 9 - 1)$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow {d_1} \times {d_2} =  - 2\widehat i - 14\widehat j - 10\widehat k$$<br><br>Now, <br><br>$$\left| {{d_1} \times {d_2}} \right| = \sqrt {{{( - 2)}^2} + {{( - 14)}^2} + {{( - 10)}^2}} $$<br><br>$$ = \sqrt {4 + 196 + 100}  = \sqrt {300} $$<br><br>$$ = 10\sqrt 3 $$<br><br>Hence, area of parallelogram <br><br>$$ = {1 \over 2} \times 10\sqrt 3  = 5\sqrt 3 $$ sq. units

Since, $$a\widehat i + \widehat j + \widehat k$$, $$\widehat i + b\widehat j + \widehat k$$ and $$\widehat i + \widehat j + c\widehat k$$ are coplanar.<br><br>$$\therefore$$ $$\left| {\matrix{
   a &amp; 1 &amp; 1  \cr 
   1 &amp; b &amp; 1  \cr 
   1 &amp; 1 &amp; c  \cr 

 } } \right| = 0$$<br><br>On applying C<sub>2</sub> $$\to$$ C<sub>2</sub> $$-$$ C<sub>1</sub>, C<sub>3</sub> $$\to$$ C<sub>3</sub> $$-$$ C<sub>1</sub>, we get<br><br>$$\left| {\matrix{
   a &amp; {1 - a} &amp; {1 - a}  \cr 
   1 &amp; {b - 1} &amp; 0  \cr 
   1 &amp; 0 &amp; {c - 1}  \cr 

 } } \right| = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow a(b - 1)(c - 1) - (1 - a)(c - 1) - (1 - a)(b - 1) = 0$$<br><br>on dividing by $$(1 - a)(1 - b)(1 - c)$$, we get<br><br>$${a \over {1 - a}} + {1 \over {1 - b}} + {1 \over {1 - c}} = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow {{1 - 1 + a} \over {1 - a}} + {1 \over {1 - b}} + {1 \over {1 - c}} = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow {1 \over {1 - a}} - 1 + {1 \over {1 - b}} + {1 \over {1 - c}} = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow {1 \over {1 - a}} + {1 \over {1 - b}} + {1 \over {1 - c}} = 1$$

a, b and c are coplanar if $$[a\,b\,c] = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow \left| {\matrix{
   1 &amp; { - 1} &amp; 1  \cr 
   2 &amp; 3 &amp; 2  \cr 
   1 &amp; m &amp; n  \cr 

 } } \right| = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow 1(3n - 2m) + 1(2n - 2) + 1(2m - 3) = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow 5n - 5 = 0$$<br><br>$$\therefore$$ n = 1<br><br>Now, $$c = \widehat i + m\widehat j + \widehat k$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow \left| c \right| = \sqrt {{1^2} + {m^2}{{(1)}^2}}  = \sqrt 6 $$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow \sqrt {{m^2} + 2}  = \sqrt 6  \Rightarrow {m^2} - 6 - 2 = 4$$<br><br>$$\therefore$$ $$m =  \pm \,2$$

We know that,<br><br>$$\widehat n = {{a \times b} \over {\left| {a \times b} \right|}}$$<br><br>$$a \times b = \left| {\matrix{
   {\widehat i} &amp; {\widehat j} &amp; {\widehat k}  \cr 
   2 &amp; { - 1} &amp; 1  \cr 
   3 &amp; { - 4} &amp; { - 1}  \cr 

 } } \right|$$<br><br>$$a \times b = 5\widehat i + 5\widehat j - 5\widehat k$$<br><br>$$\left| {a \times b} \right| = 5\sqrt 3 $$<br><br>$$\therefore$$ $$\widehat n = {{5(\widehat i + \widehat j - \widehat k)} \over {5\sqrt 3 }}$$<br><br>$$ = {{\widehat i + \widehat j - \widehat k} \over {\sqrt 3 }}$$

Given that, <br><br>$$r = (2\widehat i - \widehat j - 3\widehat k) - (\widehat i + 2\widehat j - \widehat k)$$<br><br>$$ = \widehat i - 3\widehat j + 4\widehat k$$ and $$F = 3\widehat i + \widehat k$$<br><br>$$\therefore$$ Moment $$\tau  = r \times F$$<br><br>$$ = (\widehat i - 3\widehat j + 4\widehat k) \times (3\widehat i + \widehat k)$$<br><br>$$ = \left| {\matrix{
   {\widehat i} &amp; {\widehat j} &amp; {\widehat k}  \cr 
   1 &amp; { - 3} &amp; 4  \cr 
   3 &amp; 0 &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right|$$<br><br>$$ = \widehat i( - 3 - 0) - \widehat j(1 - 12) + \widehat k(0 + 9)$$<br><br>$$ =  - 3\widehat i + 11\widehat j + 9\widehat k$$
